			<ns0:name>k...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112873510090665368075/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We are doing this because this capability is offered by GCC. We've avoided instructions with two prefixes because they can interact in unusual way, but word atomics can not be implemented in any other way: the only way to implement atomic operations with words is via command with two prefixes.

We can not actually wait till real programs which needs this will be found because it takes months to push validator update in the wild.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-08-19T19:06:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-08-19T19:06:28.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 10 by k...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=371#c10" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/371/comments/full/10" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>